# INSTRUCTIONS: Create a program using maths and f-Strings that tells us how many weeks we have left, if we live until 90 years old.
# It will take your current age as the input and output a message with our time left in this format:
# You have x weeks left.
# Where x is replaced with the actual calculated number of weeks the input age has left until age 90.

age = input() # user's age
# 🚨 Don't change the code above 👆
# Write your code below this line 👇
 
dying_age = 90
years_left = 90 - int(age)
weeks_left = int(years_left * 52) # PS.: there are 52 weeks in one year.
print(f"You have {weeks_left} weeks left.") # f" allows you to insert a variable inside {} in print() function. 
                                            # It is an easier way to insert integer or float numbers in printing.
